--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This file lists changes made to the Ansible role. It follows semantic versioning
guidelines. The content is sorted in reverse chronological order and formatted
to allow easy grepping by scripts.

The fields are:
B: bug
C: change
E: enhancement
F: feature

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Version 1.11.0 (2020-12-31)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.2-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE

* Version 1.10.1 (2020-11-29)
B: Adjust return code for monit service check

* Version 1.10.0 (2020-11-28)
F: Add support for Monit service monitoring (nsd_monitor_monit_state)

* Version 1.9.2 (2020-11-19)
E: Ensure lineinfile tasks can create file if missing

* Version 1.9.1 (2020-10-30)
E: Simplify Ansible file header (ansible_managed)

* Version 1.9.0 (2020-10-19)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.8
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.7

* Version 1.8.0 (2020-05-19)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.7
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.6

* Version 1.7.0 (2020-03-04)
F: Add support for CAA record type

* Version 1.6.1 (2020-02-19)
B: Fix POSIX permissions and group for config files on OpenBSD

* Version 1.6.0 (2019-11-08)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE

* Version 1.5.0 (2019-10-18)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.6
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.5

* Version 1.4.0 (2019-09-18)
C: Add support for managing 'unbound'
E: Utilize 'validate' parameter

* Version 1.3.0 (2019-05-26)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.8

* Version 1.2.0 (2019-04-27)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.5
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.4

* Version 1.1.0 (2019-01-13)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 11.2-RELEASE

* Version 1.0.0 (2018-12-27)
C: Mark Ansible role as 'stable'
E: Minor style improvement

* Version 0.3.1 (2018-11-30)
E: Define default value for 'item.state' parameter

* Version 0.3.0 (2018-10-20)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.4
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.3

* Version 0.2.3 (2018-08-21)
B: Correct comment symbol in zone file
E: Improve spacing in zone file (replace white spaces with tabs)

* Version 0.2.2 (2018-08-20)
B: Remove needless 'register' parameter

* Version 0.2.1 (2018-08-20)
B: Correct 'config' destination path on OpenBSD
B: Remove 'nsd_control_enable' option on OpenBSD (rcctl requires 'control-enable: yes')

* Version 0.2.0 (2018-08-20)
C: Add support for 'zone' option (nsd_zone)

* Version 0.1.0 (2018-08-19)
F: Initial release
